parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle is in motion, and can lead to fatalities.
symptoms: The engine acts like it's going to cut off
loss of engine vacuum
hesitation when taking off from a stop
uncertainty about whether the vehicle will accelerate or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Noise and Oil Pump Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine noise and oil pump issues can lead to engine failure, which can cause accidents and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine noise similar to a diesel engine
knocking sound when the vehicle is started
oil pump issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle fires can cause fatalities, injuries, and property damage.
symptoms: Vehicle caught on fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences extended stopping distances
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the ABS brakes resist or malfunction
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the airbags do not deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to the occupants.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
even when the vehicle is severely damaged
occupants may experience injuries or fatalities that could have been prevented by airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat can cause occupants to be improperly restrained, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat gives way or collapses during a crash
occupants may experience injuries or fatalities due to improper restraint.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Suspension Failure due to Rust and Weak Metal
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension components, such as the shock absorber bracket, can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and potentially result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Noise from the front end
vibration while driving
uneven tire wear
and difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and potentially result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Noise from the rear end
vibration while driving
uneven tire wear
and difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wiper system can reduce visibility during rain or wind, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers fail to operate when it is raining or windy
no indication of wiper failure
wipers may work intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A leak in the windshield can cause water to enter the vehicle, potentially damaging electrical components and creating a safety hazard.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle through the windshield.
